\b \cf0 Financial Problems\

\b0 \
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\pardirnatural
\cf0 	At the time of Lund\'92s construction, Gustavus was anything but rich. Spending over $77,000 a year on only interest at a time of high inflation rates, war, and not as many students applying to Gustavus, was not the ideal situation to be sitting financially comfortable. There were even rumors the college might have to quit operations due to little to no cash. This did not happen and under the command of Presidents Edward A. Lindell (1975-1980) and John S. Kendall (1981-1991), the college was able to stay afloat and thrive. \
\

